y Firestone]], American sportscaster and journalist * 1953 &ndash; [[Norman Finkelstein]], American author, academic, and activist * 1953 &ndash; [[Sam Kinison]], American comedian (d. 1992) * 1953 &ndash; [[Władysław Kozakiewicz]], Lithuanian-Polish pole vaulter and coach * 1953 &ndash; [[Steve Yates (footballer, born 1953)|Steve Yates]], English footballer *[[1954]] &ndash; [[Harold Hongju Koh]], American lawyer, academic, and politician * 1954 &ndash; [[Frits Pirard]], Dutch cyclist *[[1955]] &ndash; [[Kasim Sulton]], American singer-songwriter, bass player, and producer * 1955 &ndash; [[Milenko Zablaćanski]], Serbian actor, director, and screenwriter (d. 2008) *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Warren Cuccurullo]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist * 1956 &ndash; [[Andrius Kubilius]], Lithuanian academic and politician, [[Prime Minister of Lithuania|9th Prime Minister of Lithuania]] * 1956 &ndash; [[Slick (wrestling)|Slick]], American wrestler and manager *[[1957]] &ndash; [[James Cama]], American martial artist and educator (d. 2014) * 1957 &ndash; [[Phil Collen]], English singer-songwriter and guitarist *[[1958]] &ndash; [[Rob Byrnes]], American author and blogger * 1958 &ndash; [[Rob Curling]], Malayan-English journalist * 1958 &ndash; [[Michel Ferté]], French race car driver * 1958 &ndash; [[Bob Greene (fitness)|Bob Greene]], American physiologist and author * 1958 &ndash; [[Mirosław Okoński]], Polish footballer *[[1959]] &ndash; [[Stephen Jefferies]], South African cricketer and coach * 1959 &ndash; [[Mark Steyn]], Canadian-American author and critic *[[1960]] &ndash; [[Aaron Allston]], American game designer and author (d. 2014) * 1960 &ndash; [[Lim Guan Eng]], Malaysian accountant and politician, 4th [[Chief Minister of the State of Penang]] and incumbent [[Minister of Finance]]. * 1960 &ndash; [[Bill McKibben]], American author and environmentalist *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Ann Coulter]], American lawyer, journalist, and author * 1961 &ndash; [[Mikey Robins]], Austral